The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Plateau State has assured all gubernatorial aspirants and others seeking elective positions under the party’s platform of a level playing ground ahead of the 2023 general elections. The Party also advised aspirants and their supporters against violence and calumny as they go about their campaigns. Chairman of the APC in Plateau, Rufus Bature gave the advice on Wednesday in Jos, when an aspirant Mr. Sunday Garba Biggs, officially informed the State Executive Committee of the party of his intention to vie for governor. Bature said, “under my watch, the party would allow the people to make their choice, and instead of individuals. The chairman urged Biggs and his team to campaign vigorously to win the party’s ticket to fly APC’s flag in the 2023 general election. He appreciated Biggs for informing the party of his intention.